<h1>go-httpbin(1){{if .Version}} <small>v{{.Version}}</small>{{end}}</h1>
<p>A golang port of the venerable <a href="https://httpbin.org/">httpbin.org</a> HTTP request &amp; response testing service.</p>

<h2 id="ENDPOINTS">ENDPOINTS</h2>

<p><strong>Note:</strong> All endpoints accept an optional <code>?response_delay=&lt;duration&gt;</code> query parameter to add an initial delay before responding (e.g. <code>?response_delay=2s</code> or <code>?response_delay=1-5</code> for a random delay).</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/"><code>{{.Prefix}}/</code></a> This page.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/absolute-redirect/6"><code>{{.Prefix}}/absolute-redirect/:n</code></a> 302 Absolute redirects <em>n</em> times.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/anything"><code>{{.Prefix}}/anything/:anything</code></a> Returns anything that is passed to request.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/base64/eyJzZXJ2ZXIiOiAiZ28taHR0cGJpbiJ9Cg==?content-type=application/json"><code>{{.Prefix}}/base64/:value?content-type=ct</code></a> Decodes a Base64-encoded string, with optional Content-Type.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/base64/decode/aHR0cGJpbmdvLm9yZw=="><code>{{.Prefix}}/base64/decode/:value?content-type=ct</code></a> Explicit URL for decoding a Base64 encoded string.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/base64/encode/httpbingo.org"><code>{{.Prefix}}/base64/encode/:value</code></a> Encodes a string into URL-safe Base64.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/basic-auth/user/password"><code>{{.Prefix}}/basic-auth/:user/:password</code></a> Challenges HTTPBasic Auth.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/bearer"><code>{{.Prefix}}/bearer</code></a> Checks Bearer token header - returns 401 if not set.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/brotli"><code><del>{{.Prefix}}/brotli</del></code></a> Returns brotli-encoded data.</del> <i>Not implemented!</i></li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/bytes/1024"><code>{{.Prefix}}/bytes/:n</code></a> Generates <em>n</em> random bytes of binary data, accepts optional <em>seed</em> integer parameter.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/cache"><code>{{.Prefix}}/cache</code></a> Returns 200 unless an If-Modified-Since or If-None-Match header is provided, when it returns a 304.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/cache/60"><code>{{.Prefix}}/cache/:n</code></a> Sets a Cache-Control header for <em>n</em> seconds.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/close"><code>{{.Prefix}}/close?mode=clean|reset&amp;after=headers|partial</code></a> Closes the connection abruptly, optionally after sending headers or partial data.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/cookies"><code>{{.Prefix}}/cookies</code></a> Returns cookie data.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/cookies/delete?k1=&amp;k2="><code>{{.Prefix}}/cookies/delete?name</code></a> Deletes one or more simple cookies.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/cookies/set?k1=v1&amp;k2=v2"><code>{{.Prefix}}/cookies/set?name=value</code></a> Sets one or more simple cookies.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/deflate"><code>{{.Prefix}}/deflate</code></a> Returns deflate-encoded data.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/delay/3"><code>{{.Prefix}}/delay/:n</code></a> Delays responding for <em>min(n, 10)</em> seconds. Supports range syntax like <em>2-8</em> for random delays.</li>
<li><code>{{.Prefix}}/delete</code> Returns request data.  Allows only <code>DELETE</code> requests.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/deny"><code>{{.Prefix}}/deny</code></a> Denied by robots.txt file.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/digest-auth/auth/user/password"><code>{{.Prefix}}/digest-auth/:qop/:user/:password</code></a> Challenges HTTP Digest Auth using default MD5 algorithm</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/digest-auth/auth/user/password/SHA-256"><code>{{.Prefix}}/digest-auth/:qop/:user/:password/:algorithm</code></a> Challenges HTTP Digest Auth using specified algorithm (MD5 or SHA-256)</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/drip?code=200&amp;numbytes=5&amp;duration=5"><code>{{.Prefix}}/drip?numbytes=n&amp;duration=s&amp;delay=s&amp;code=code</code></a> Drips data over the given duration after an optional initial delay, simulating a slow HTTP server.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/dump/request"><code>{{.Prefix}}/dump/request</code></a> Returns the given request in its HTTP/1.x wire approximate representation.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/echo"><code>{{.Prefix}}/echo</code></a> Echoes the request body back with the same Content-Type. Allows <code>POST</code>, <code>PUT</code>, <code>PATCH</code>.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/encoding/utf8"><code>{{.Prefix}}/encoding/utf8</code></a> Returns page containing UTF-8 data.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/env"><code>{{.Prefix}}/env</code></a> Returns all environment variables named with <code>HTTPBIN_ENV_</code> prefix.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/etag/etag"><code>{{.Prefix}}/etag/:etag</code></a> Assumes the resource has the given etag and responds to If-None-Match header with a 200 or 304 and If-Match with a 200 or 412 as appropriate.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/forms/post"><code>{{.Prefix}}/forms/post</code></a> HTML form that submits to <em>{{.Prefix}}/post</em></li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/get"><code>{{.Prefix}}/get</code></a> Returns GET data.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/gzip"><code>{{.Prefix}}/gzip</code></a> Returns gzip-encoded data.</li>
<li><code>{{.Prefix}}/head</code> Returns response headers.  Allows only <code>HEAD</code> requests.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/headers"><code>{{.Prefix}}/headers</code></a> Returns request header dict.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/hidden-basic-auth/user/password"><code>{{.Prefix}}/hidden-basic-auth/:user/:password</code></a> 404'd BasicAuth.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/html"><code>{{.Prefix}}/html</code></a> Renders an HTML Page.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/hostname"><code>{{.Prefix}}/hostname</code></a> Returns the name of the host serving the request.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/image"><code>{{.Prefix}}/image</code></a> Returns page containing an image based on sent Accept header. Accepts <code>?size=small|medium|large</code>, <code>?gradient=preset</code>, <code>?color1=hex&amp;color2=hex</code>, <code>?noise=0-255</code>, <code>?nocache=1</code>.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/image/avif"><code>{{.Prefix}}/image/avif</code></a> Returns an AVIF image.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/image/jpeg"><code>{{.Prefix}}/image/jpeg</code></a> Returns a JPEG image. Accepts <code>?size=small|medium|large</code>.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/image/png"><code>{{.Prefix}}/image/png</code></a> Returns a PNG image. Accepts <code>?size=small|medium|large</code>.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/image/svg"><code>{{.Prefix}}/image/svg</code></a> Returns a SVG image.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/image/webp"><code>{{.Prefix}}/image/webp</code></a> Returns a WEBP image.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/image/photo.png"><code>{{.Prefix}}/image/photo.{ext}</code></a> Returns an image based on file extension (.png, .jpeg, .jpg, .svg, .webp, .avif).</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/image/size/small/photo.png"><code>{{.Prefix}}/image/size/{small|medium|large}/filename.{ext}</code></a> Returns a generated image of the given size.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/image/gradient/warm/size/small/photo.png"><code>{{.Prefix}}/image/gradient/{preset}/size/{size}/filename.{ext}</code></a> Returns a generated image with a gradient preset (warm, cool, sunset, forest, ocean, grayscale, neon).</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/image/no-cache/size/small/photo.png"><code>{{.Prefix}}/image/no-cache/.../filename.{ext}</code></a> Returns a unique (uncached) generated image.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/ip"><code>{{.Prefix}}/ip</code></a> Returns Origin IP.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/json"><code>{{.Prefix}}/json</code></a> Returns JSON.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/links/10"><code>{{.Prefix}}/links/:n</code></a> Returns page containing <em>n</em> HTML links.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/mix/s=200/h=X-Custom:value/d=1s"><code>{{.Prefix}}/mix/s=:code/h=:header:value/d=:delay/b64=:body</code></a> Composable endpoint that combines status code, headers, delays, and body in a single URL.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/negotiate"><code>{{.Prefix}}/negotiate</code></a> Performs content negotiation based on the Accept header.</li>
<li><code>{{.Prefix}}/patch</code> Returns request data.  Allows only <code>PATCH</code> requests.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/pdf"><code>{{.Prefix}}/pdf?pages=n&amp;size=small|medium|large&amp;seed=int&amp;nocache=1</code></a> Returns a dynamically generated PDF document. <em>pages</em> (1-100, default 1), <em>size</em> (content density), <em>seed</em> (deterministic, default 42), <em>nocache</em> or <em>no-cache</em> (unique each time).</li>
<li><code>{{.Prefix}}/post</code> Returns request data.  Allows only <code>POST</code> requests.</li>
<li><code>{{.Prefix}}/put</code> Returns request data.  Allows only <code>PUT</code> requests.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/problem?status=422&amp;title=Validation+Failed"><code>{{.Prefix}}/problem?status=:code&amp;title=:title&amp;detail=:detail</code></a> Returns a Problem Details (RFC 9457) JSON response. Pipeline-compatible: <code>/status/422/problem?title=Test</code> sets both HTTP and JSON status.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/range/:n"><code>{{.Prefix}}/range/1024?duration=s&amp;chunk_size=code</code></a> Streams <em>n</em> bytes, and allows specifying a <em>Range</em> header to select a subset of the data. Accepts a <em>chunk_size</em> and request <em>duration</em> parameter.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/redirect-to?status_code=307&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fexample.com%2F"><code>{{.Prefix}}/redirect-to?url=foo&status_code=307</code></a> 307 Redirects to the <em>foo</em> URL.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/redirect-to?url=http%3A%2F%2Fexample.com%2F"><code>{{.Prefix}}/redirect-to?url=foo</code></a> 302 Redirects to the <em>foo</em> URL.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/redirect/6"><code>{{.Prefix}}/redirect/:n</code></a> 302 Redirects <em>n</em> times.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/relative-redirect/6"><code>{{.Prefix}}/relative-redirect/:n</code></a> 302 Relative redirects <em>n</em> times.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/response-headers?Server=httpbin&amp;Content-Type=text%2Fplain%3B+charset%3DUTF-8"><code>{{.Prefix}}/response-headers?key=val</code></a> Returns given response headers.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/robots.txt"><code>{{.Prefix}}/robots.txt</code></a> Returns some robots.txt rules.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/sse?delay=1s&amp;duration=5s&count=10"><code>{{.Prefix}}/sse?delay=1s&amp;duration=5s&amp;count=10&amp;event=name&amp;retry=ms&amp;fail_after=n</code></a> a stream of server-sent events.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/status/418"><code>{{.Prefix}}/status/:code</code></a> Returns given HTTP Status code.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/stream-bytes/1024"><code>{{.Prefix}}/stream-bytes/:n</code></a> Streams <em>n</em> random bytes of binary data, accepts optional <em>seed</em> and <em>chunk_size</em> integer parameters.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/stream/20"><code>{{.Prefix}}/stream/:n</code></a> Streams <em>min(n, 100)</em> lines.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/trailers?trailer1=value1&amp;trailer2=value2"><code>{{.Prefix}}/trailers?key=val</code></a> Returns JSON response with query params added as HTTP Trailers.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/unstable"><code>{{.Prefix}}/unstable</code></a> Fails half the time, accepts optional <em>failure_rate</em> float and <em>seed</em> integer parameters.</li>
<li><code>{{.Prefix}}/upload</code> Discards the body of <code>POST</code>/<code>PUT</code>/<code>PATCH</code> requests, for testing upload performance.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/user-agent"><code>{{.Prefix}}/user-agent</code></a> Returns user-agent.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/uuid"><code>{{.Prefix}}/uuid</code></a> Generates a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Universally_unique_identifier">UUIDv4</a> value.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/version"><code>{{.Prefix}}/version</code></a> Returns the version of the go-httpbin instance. Pipeline-compatible (e.g. <code>/delay/1/version</code>).</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/websocket/echo?max_fragment_size=2048&amp;max_message_size=10240"><code>{{.Prefix}}/websocket/echo?max_fragment_size=2048&amp;max_message_size=10240</code></a> A WebSocket echo service.</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/xml"><code>{{.Prefix}}/xml</code></a> Returns some XML</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="DESCRIPTION">DESCRIPTION</h2>

<p>Testing an HTTP Library can become difficult sometimes. <a href="http://requestb.in">RequestBin</a> is fantastic for testing POST requests, but doesn't let you control the response. This exists to cover all kinds of HTTP scenarios. Additional endpoints are being considered.</p>

<p>All endpoint responses are JSON-encoded.</p>

<h2 id="EXAMPLES">EXAMPLES</h2>

<h3 id="-curl-http-httpbin-org-ip">$ curl http://localhost:8080/ip</h3>

<pre><code>{"origin":"73.238.9.52, 77.83.142.42"}
</code></pre>

<h3 id="-curl-http-httpbin-org-user-agent">$ curl http://localhost:8080/user-agent</h3>

<pre><code>{"user-agent":"curl/7.64.1"}</code></pre>

<h3 id="-curl-http-httpbin-org-get">$ curl http://localhost:8080/get?foo=bar</h3>

<pre><code>{
  "args": {
    "foo": [
      "bar"
    ]
  },
  "headers": {
    "Accept": [
      "*/*"
    ],
    "Host": [
      "localhost:8080"
    ],
    "User-Agent": [
      "curl/7.64.1"
    ]
  },
  "origin": "73.238.9.52, 77.83.142.42",
  "url": "http://localhost:8080/get?foo=bar"
}
</code></pre>

<h3 id="-curl-http-httpbin-org-dump-request">$ curl http://localhost:8080/dump/request?foo=bar</h3>

<pre><code>GET /dump/request?foo=bar HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:8080
Accept: */*
User-Agent: curl/7.64.1
</code></pre>

<h3 id="-curl-I-http-httpbin-org-status-418">$ curl -I http://localhost:8080/status/418</h3>

<pre><code>HTTP/1.1 418 I'm a teapot
Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true
Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
X-More-Info: http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2324
Date: Tue, 13 Jul 2021 13:12:37 GMT
Content-Length: 0
</code></pre>

<h3>$ curl http://localhost:8080/version</h3>
<pre><code>{"version":"abc1234","go_version":"go1.26"}</code></pre>

<h3>$ curl -o doc.pdf "http://localhost:8080/pdf?pages=3&amp;size=large"</h3>
<pre><code># Downloads a 3-page large PDF document</code></pre>

<h3>$ curl http://localhost:8080/problem?status=422&amp;title=Validation+Failed</h3>
<pre><code>{"type":"about:blank","title":"Validation Failed","status":422,"detail":""}</code></pre>

<h3>$ curl -X POST -H 'Content-Type: text/plain' -d 'hello' http://localhost:8080/echo</h3>
<pre><code>hello</code></pre>

<h2 id="PIPELINE">PIPELINE: COMPOSABLE URLs</h2>

<p>Chain operations directly in the URL path. Prefix any endpoint
with one or more <strong>modifiers</strong> to compose behavior, then
specify a <strong>terminal</strong> endpoint.</p>

<h3>Modifiers</h3>
<ul>
<li><code>delay/:duration</code> &mdash; Add a delay (e.g. <code>delay/1</code>, <code>delay/500ms</code>, <code>delay/2-4</code> for random range)</li>
<li><code>response_delay/:duration</code> &mdash; Same as delay (alternative name)</li>
<li><code>status/:code</code> &mdash; Override the response status code</li>
<li><code>header/:name:value</code> &mdash; Set a custom response header (X-* headers or allowlisted names)</li>
<li><code>no-cache</code> &mdash; Disable caching (equivalent to <code>?nocache=1</code>)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Terminals</h3>
<p>All single endpoints work as terminals. Grouped by category:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Request inspection:</strong> get, post, put, delete, patch, head, headers, ip, user-agent, anything, dump/request</li>
<li><strong>Data formats:</strong> json, xml, html, gzip, deflate, encoding/utf8, body/:base64</li>
<li><strong>Images:</strong> image, image/:kind, image/size/:size/photo.:ext, image/gradient/:preset/...</li>
<li><strong>Documents:</strong> pdf</li>
<li><strong>Info:</strong> version, hostname, uuid, env, bearer, negotiate</li>
<li><strong>Status &amp; redirects:</strong> status/:code, redirect/:n, absolute-redirect/:n, relative-redirect/:n, redirect-to, response-headers</li>
<li><strong>Auth:</strong> basic-auth/:u/:p, hidden-basic-auth/:u/:p, digest-auth/:qop/:u/:p</li>
<li><strong>Streaming:</strong> bytes/:n, stream/:n, stream-bytes/:n, range/:n, drip, sse</li>
<li><strong>Cookies:</strong> cookies, cookies/set, cookies/delete</li>
<li><strong>Echo/Upload:</strong> echo (POST/PUT/PATCH), upload (POST/PUT/PATCH)</li>
<li><strong>Connection:</strong> close, problem</li>
<li><strong>Other:</strong> robots.txt, deny, cache, etag/:etag, links/:n, unstable, trailers</li>
</ul>

<h3>Error responses</h3>
<ul>
<li><code>400</code> &mdash; Invalid modifier value, unknown segment, missing terminal</li>
<li><code>405</code> &mdash; Wrong HTTP method for a method-restricted terminal (e.g. GET on /echo)</li>
<li><code>501</code> &mdash; AVIF/WebP generation without conversion tools</li>
</ul>

<h3>Examples</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/delay/1/status/418"><code>{{.Prefix}}/delay/1/status/418</code></a> &mdash; Wait 1s, then return 418 I'm a Teapot</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/delay/500ms/get"><code>{{.Prefix}}/delay/500ms/get</code></a> &mdash; Wait 500ms, then return request data</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/status/422/body/SGVsbG8="><code>{{.Prefix}}/status/422/body/SGVsbG8=</code></a> &mdash; Return "Hello" with status 422</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/header/X-Custom:test/status/201/get"><code>{{.Prefix}}/header/X-Custom:test/status/201/get</code></a> &mdash; Custom header + status override + GET data</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/delay/1/version"><code>{{.Prefix}}/delay/1/version</code></a> &mdash; Wait 1s, then return version info</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/status/422/problem?title=Validation+Failed"><code>{{.Prefix}}/status/422/problem?title=Validation+Failed</code></a> &mdash; HTTP 422 + coherent Problem Details JSON</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/delay/0/response-headers?X-Debug=true"><code>{{.Prefix}}/delay/0/response-headers?X-Debug=true</code></a> &mdash; Custom response headers via pipeline</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/status/201/pdf?pages=3"><code>{{.Prefix}}/status/201/pdf?pages=3</code></a> &mdash; 3-page PDF with status 201</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/header/X-Request-Id:abc/status/200/json"><code>{{.Prefix}}/header/X-Request-Id:abc/status/200/json</code></a> &mdash; JSON with custom header and status</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/image/gradient/warm/size/small/photo.png"><code>{{.Prefix}}/image/gradient/warm/size/small/photo.png</code></a> &mdash; Warm gradient PNG image</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/image/no-cache/gradient/cool/size/small/photo.jpeg"><code>{{.Prefix}}/image/no-cache/gradient/cool/size/small/photo.jpeg</code></a> &mdash; Unique cool gradient JPEG</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/redirect/3/status/200"><code>{{.Prefix}}/redirect/3/status/200</code></a> &mdash; Redirect 3 times, ending with status 200</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/delay/1/redirect/3/image/photo.png"><code>{{.Prefix}}/delay/1/redirect/3/image/photo.png</code></a> &mdash; Wait 1s, redirect 3 times, serve PNG image</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/delay/2-4/bytes/1024"><code>{{.Prefix}}/delay/2-4/bytes/1024</code></a> &mdash; Random 2-4s delay, then 1024 random bytes</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/status/201/json"><code>{{.Prefix}}/status/201/json</code></a> &mdash; JSON with status 201</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/delay/500ms/status/503"><code>{{.Prefix}}/delay/500ms/status/503</code></a> &mdash; Wait 500ms + server error</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/header/X-Debug:true/uuid"><code>{{.Prefix}}/header/X-Debug:true/uuid</code></a> &mdash; UUID with custom header</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/delay/0/hostname"><code>{{.Prefix}}/delay/0/hostname</code></a> &mdash; Hostname via pipeline</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/delay/0/negotiate"><code>{{.Prefix}}/delay/0/negotiate</code></a> &mdash; Content negotiation via pipeline</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/status/422/problem?title=Validation+Failed"><code>{{.Prefix}}/status/422/problem?title=Validation+Failed</code></a> &mdash; Coherent Problem Details</li>
<li><a href="{{.Prefix}}/no-cache/pdf?pages=3"><code>{{.Prefix}}/no-cache/pdf?pages=3</code></a> &mdash; Unique PDF each time via pipeline modifier</li>
<li><code>{{.Prefix}}/pdf?pages=5&amp;size=large&amp;no-cache=1</code> &mdash; PDF with no-cache query param</li>
<li><code>{{.Prefix}}/delay/abc/get</code> &mdash; 400 error: invalid delay value</li>
<li><code>{{.Prefix}}/delay/999/get</code> &mdash; 400 error: delay exceeds maximum</li>
</ul>

<h3>Known Limitations</h3>
<ul>
<li>Browsers (Chrome, Edge) won't render binary content (PDF, images) inline with non-200 status codes. Use <code>curl</code> to verify the response. This is a browser limitation, not a server bug.</li>
</ul>

